        "committer": {
          "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
          "email": "gregoire.pichon@bull.net",
          "date": "2015-03-06 15:04:48.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 ptlrpc: fix NUMA binding policy to use CPT",
        "message": "LU-0000 ptlrpc: fix NUMA binding policy to use CPT\n\nThe ptlrpcd binding policy PDB_POLICY_NEIGHBOR does not correctly\nmanage offline cpus when kernel supports NUMA.\n\nThis patch implements a separate policy PDB_POLICY_CPT that relies\non the libcfs compute partition table. With that policy, each ptlrpcd\nthread is bound to a cpu of the cptable. Its partners are all the\nthreads bound to a cpu of the same cpt. Additionnaly this policy take\ncare of NUMA binding.\n\nSigned-off-by: Gregoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nChange-Id: Ib3b3f15c1b19beeda3a7fa40a438a6dc07031974\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
